All in our plan for a quick 30 min meal took over an hour. Oh, and it ain't cheap.

Had Saturday brunch and Monday morning breakfast here. First off, the food and drinks were PHENOMENAL. We were not disappointed either time! During brunch, we split the Crabby Wife and the cornbread waffle with beef on it. Tons of flavor and huge portions. I also had a bloody mary--tasty without being pretentious, and just the right amount of spice--followed by an iced cannon to go (gotta love NOLA!), which was strong, creamy, and wonderful. At breakfast, we split a fruit parfait (gorgeous presentation and absolutely delicious) and their BEC breakfast sandwich, piled high on a delectable marble rye. Good coffee, too. My only complaint is the service. During brunch, they were busy (which I totally understand), but the people seated next to us (one foot away) got waters, menus, and drinks before we got anything. Luckily a really friendly gentleman with salt-and-pepper hair (the owner?) noticed fairly quickly and promptly took our order immediately thereafter. Breakfast was a whole different story. When we walked in there were literally two tables of people in the entire restaurant, both of whom had already been served. No one greeted us (though both the female servers looked straight at us), so we finally just took a seat. 10 MINUTES LATER we were begrudgingly given menus, and coffee took another 15 minutes even though we asked for it when given menus. Note that another table of people who arrived after us were seated, given menus/coffee, and had their food DELIVERED before we even got our coffee. Unacceptable and inexcusable!!! Overall, I'd give five stars for food but only 2-3 stars for service.

I am only giving this restaurant one star because I can’t give it zero.  I traveled to New Orleans to visit family this weekend and on our way out we decided to take advantage of a good southern breakfast. We always choose a new restaurant to try when we come in.  My mom, sister, two daughters and I decided on “Horns”.We had to put our name down for a 30 to 45 min wait but we were super ok with that because usually when you have a line out here it just means it’s worth the wait. Well not this time.  We were seated by the most wonderful gentleman and quickly introduced us to our waitresses. After taking our order, she brought over our drinks first. The glasses we received were not the ones we fell in love with when we walked in the door. This was why we ordered the mimosas. It was so beautifully sitting on another customer’s table. We asked her if she had given us a different drink by mistake. She advised us that the bar tender stated that it was that same amount of liquid in this glass as the other and she would not give us the other glass. Perplexed at this we asked why. She stated that she did not know why. We asked if she could provide us with the drinks we requested. She urgently took the drinks back to the bar. About 30 secs later the bar tender brought the empty glasses we asked for to our table and poured the liquid from the other glass into them. Waisting liquid on my mother as she poured with a agitated look on her face. We were flabbergasted and also floored.... at her dramatic display of aggression. She then slammed the glass on the table with a hard thud. We were disoriented at this but we understand that at times in customer service you get tired so we were going to let it go. However, when my sister looked at her glass she saw things floating in it. She gestured to our waitress to return to the table and showed her what she had found. This made me want to inspect my glass as well. Upon review, it was full of grease and grit as well. It looked as if it was taken out of the sink and placed on our table without a rinse or wash at all. This was the last straw. I calmly stood up and told my family “let’s go”. I brought the glass to the bar and politely stated “ this glass” as I placed it on the bar with a loud thud, “is dirty. It is full of grease and grit. We are leaving, thank you.” I turned and walked away.  This was by far the worst experience we have ever had in all of our visits to New Orleans. The way we were treated was unwarranted and appalling. The service you receive has a huge part to play on how well you view the whole meal experience.  My advise is to never visit this restaurant. With employees like this, what should we think of the owners?

Favorite brunch spot in New Orleans by a long shot! I absolutely love the staff here and the overall vibe. A personal favorite of mine is the Waffles Cochon which is pulled pork over cornbread waffle with a poached eggs and pickled peppers with chimichury. Yum!
I love love love love this quantity eatery!!!! Crabby Wife...you I will never divorce!!! Crab cake covered in shrimp etouffee with poached eggs.   HEAVEN.

The corn waffles with fruit were a memorable breakfast! There was a waiting list to get inside, so we opted for outside seating. Took a bit for a waitress to come out and seat us. In the meantime a couple decide to plop themselves down in the empty table outside while they waited to get in. But the waitress was on the ball, noted that we were first on the list and politely informed them they would have to vacate. Good for us! Once seated, the service was flawless. The food came out pretty quick. The waitress checked up on us and asked if we needed anything. I said "Yeah, a flyswatter would be nice." She laughed it off like it was a joke. But quite seriously, other cafes around New Orleans do not have a problem with leaving a flyswatter in plain sight. If I could have quickly taken care of the 4 huge flys that were obviously regular patrons of the establishment, it certainly would have made for a much more peaceful breakfast experience. Still when you walk away feeling slightly high because the food was so good, can't let a minor irritation like that take a notch off a 5 star revue.
Really loved this place. Unique charm and great menu.
The food was amazing!!! I had the crabby wife and cornbread and it was delicious, highly recommend this place when visiting New Orleans!

Today may have been an off day. I believe in 2nd chances so we'll try it again. The burger is mediocre at best and very simple. Asked the server if it came with fries and she said no so I ordered some...it came with chips so it was a bit of a starch overload for lunch. The grilled chicken Caesar salad and the meatloaf looked very good.

Amazing food! Amazing service. Our waitress was incredibly attentive with a smile on her face. We went for lunch on a Tuesday, it was busy but not too busy. My mother in law was very impressed saying it was the best fish she had had on our trip to New Orleans

What can we say we've been here twice in 2 years and loved it both times. Staff is great and food awesome.  Our one must go to place when we are in town! Bring your appetite because you won't leave hungry!

I came here twice for breakfast, two days in a row. The first time it was delicious, I shared plates with two other people and all three dishes were great. The next day, I re-ordered something we had had the previous day, The Savory Breakfast. This time, it gave me food poisoning (and I have a really strong stomach, this was the first time I've ever gotten food poisoning). This also happened to be the day that I was traveling home, a journey of about 11 hours total with layovers,  which was not fun, to say the least.  I have to say, regardless of the food quality, the service here is incredible, which is why I can't justify giving it fewer than three stars. Maybe just don't order the Savory Breakfast when you go.

Had something I had never considered for breakfast before, chili.  Actually it was the Orleans Slammer which was Hash Browns, topped with black bean chili, topped with 2 eggs, 2 strips of thick cut bacon and a biscuit. It was so good my wife stole part of it from me to eat for herself. Very clean, quick service, decent coffee, no complaints.

I love diversity of my hometown. However I observed an artifact that reminded me of times when blacks were belittled. A piece constructed of bottle tops depicting a demeaning view of blacks. I noticed no blacks on the main floor but were cooking the food and washing the dishes. Placement of this object high and center of the bar is on display for all patrons. I find it offensive to my race and will not be returning.

We waited half an hour for a table which was our choice as the restaurant was very busy. After being seated server took drink order and when it arrived my wife's glass was chipped on the rim. The server then came back to the table after 15 min and apologized for the delay but food would be out shortly. Eventually after another 15/20 minutes our food arrived. We had ordered from the menu with no substitutions and it had taken over half an our to arrive and almost everything on our plates was cold. I will admit I didn't complain to server at the time as the thought of sitting there for another half an hour to get food replaced wasn't viable. Oh and btw my wife's plate was also chipped which may be a cultural thing Im not sure. I got fed up waiting for a check I went into the restaurant to pay and even that seemed to be a challenge. My advice,, go to iHop, food is comparable, cheaper and quicker

We have been going to Horn's for over a year and have raved about their awesome food and service. However, today, September 24, 2017, my wife and I where treated very rudley and unprofessionally from the owner. I was on crutches from a surgery less than a week ago and was just coming to eat breakfast after attending church and was craving Horn's. While I was crutching my way up the sidewalk, my wife went to reserve us a seat and put our names on the wait list, as we have always done. The hostess at the door said if we wanted to sit outside, to go ahead and grab an open table and not to sign the wait list. The owner came outside, approached us, and asked us very rudely if we had put our names on the wait list and my wife explained what the hostess said. The owner rudely walked off and said she would correct her hostess for allowing us to sit down. She then apologized to some women who complained that we sat down before her. Maybe the women didn't ask if her party could sit outside, or maybe the owner needs to do a better job in training her staff to all be on the same page. No matter what, local or tourist, no customer should be treated the way the owner treated us. Good food, great atmosphere, great service from the wait staff. There is a way to speak to people and this was not it. I guess some owners forget that us locals are the ones that pay the bills when they first open their business. Very, very disappointed and will never return. My wife and I deserve a hell of a lot more respect than what was given. Will make sure we let the people we refer to Horns know about today's poor performance By THE OWNER.
